label.value: thrombospondin-3 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form

value.value: A thrombospondin-3 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide removed to yield the mature protein.

label.value: thrombospondin-4 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form

value.value: A thrombospondin-4 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide removed to yield the mature protein.
A transcription factor Sp1 isoform 1 acetylated form that has been acetylated by PCAF.
A transcription factor Sp1 isoform 1 that has had the N-terminal inhibitory domain released.
A transcription factor Sp1 isoform 1 glycosylated form that has terminal O-linked N-acetylglucosamines. Example: UniProtKB:P08047-1, Ser-491, MOD:00805.
A transcription factor Sp1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs within the N-terminal activation domains by a DNA-dependent protein kinase.

A transcription factor Sp1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at a Thr residue within the C-terminal region by casein kinase II. Example: UniProtKB:P08047-1, Thr-579, MOD:00047.

A transcription factor Sp1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the Ser residue within the CyclinA/cdk2 phosphorylation site (QPSP sequence). Phosphorylation at this site induces removal of the inhibitory domain by proteolytic processing and activation of transcription activity. Example: UniProtKB:P08047-1, Ser-59, MOD:00046.
A transcription factor Sp1 isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the first serine/threonine stretch by ATM kinase in response to DNA damage.

A transcription factor Sp1 isoform 1 sumoylated form that has a SUMO protein covalently linked to a Lys residue at the consensus motif VKIE within the N-terminal inhibitory domain. Example: UniProtKB:P08047-1, Lys-16, MOD:01149.
A tumor necrosis factor isoform 1 that is the soluble C-terminal portion after processing by TNF alpha converting enzyme ADAM17.
A tumor necrosis factor isoform 1 that is the inactive soluble form after alternative protein processing. The resulting protein is 10 amino acids longer than the active form.

definition.value: Category=modification. Compare this to PR:000000604 (the active form).

value.value: A tumor necrosis factor isoform 1 myristoylated form that has been modified at the N-epsilon-NH2 groups of the most N-terminal Lys within the cytoplasmic domain. Example: UniProtKB:P01375-1, Lys-19/Lys-20, MOD:00087.

A tumor necrosis factor isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at the N-terminal Ser within the ST[EK]S motif in the cytoplasmic domain. Example: UniProtKB:P01375-1, Ser-2, MOD:00046.

value.value: A bone morphogenetic protein 2 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide and propeptide removed.

value.value: A bone morphogenetic protein 4 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide and propeptide removed.

value.value: A bone morphogenetic protein 5 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide and propeptide removed.

label.value: bone morphogenetic protein 6 isoform 1, mature form

value.value: A bone morphogenetic protein 6 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide and propeptide removed.

label.value: bone morphogenetic protein 7 isoform 1, mature form

value.value: A bone morphogenetic protein 7 isoform 1 that has had the signal peptide and propeptide removed. Example: UniProtKB:P23359-1, 292-430.

label.value: bone morphogenetic protein 7 isoform 1, mature N-glycosylated 1

value.value: A bone morphogenetic protein 7 isoform 1, mature glycosylated form that is N-glycosylated at the N{P}[ST]{P} motif. This form is a disulfide linked homodimer. Example: UniProtKB:P18075-1, 293-431, Asn-372, MOD:00160.

label.value: bone morphogenetic protein 7 isoform 1, mature N-glycosylated 2

value.value: A bone morphogenetic protein 7 isoform 1, mature glycosylated form that has the propeptide still bound to the mature protein. This form is N-glycosylated at the most C-terminal N{P}[ST]{P} motif and is a homodimer. Example: UniProtKB:P18075-1, 20-292, 293-431, Asn-372, MOD:00160.

label.value: GTP-binding protein RhoA isoform 1 prenylated-cysteine methyl ester 1

value.value: A GTP-binding protein RhoA isoform 1 that has been geranylgeranylated on the Cys residue within the C-terminal CaaX motif (a=an aliphatic residue, X=any residue), followed by cleavage of aaX and methylation of the Cys. Example: UniProtKB:P61586-1, 1-190, Cys-190, MOD:01119.
A TGF-beta 1 isoform 1 that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage and released from the latent complex. This form is the active mature protein. Example: UniProtKB:P01137-1, 279-390.

A TGF-beta 1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has had the C-terminal mature peptide removed and has been N-glycosylated mainly at either one of the two first consensus N-glycosylation sites. Example: UniProtKB:P01137-1, 30-279, Asn-82, MOD:00160.

A TGF-beta 1 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been cleaved at the dibasic cleavage site, rendering the latency associated peptide (LAP) and the mature protein non-covalently bound. This form is glycosylated mainly at either one or the two first consensus glycosylation sites within the LAP sequence. Example: UniProtKB:P01137-1, 30-278, 279-390, Asn-82, MOD:00160.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant T81H, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the latency associated peptide (LAP). UniProtKB:P01137, 279-390, Tyr-81, CHEBI:29979.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant T81H, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the C-terminal mature peptide. This chain is referred as to the latency associated peptide (LAP). UniProtKB:P01137, 30-278, Tyr-81, CHEBI:29979.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant R218C, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the latency associated peptide (LAP). UniProtKB:P01137, 279-390, Arg-218, CHEBI:29950.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant R218C, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the C-terminal mature peptide. This chain is referred as to the latency associated peptide (LAP). This form has decreased affinity for the mature peptide (PR:000000621). UniProtKB:P01137, 30-278, Arg-218, CHEBI:29950.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant H222D, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the latency associated peptide (LAP). UniProtKB:P01137, 279-390, His-222, CHEBI:29958.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant H222D, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the C-terminal mature peptide. This chain is referred as to the latency associated peptide (LAP). UniProtKB:P01137, 30-278, His-222, CHEBI:29958.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant C225R, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the latency associated peptide (LAP). UniProtKB:P01137, 279-390, Cys-225, CHEBI:29952.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant C225R, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the C-terminal mature peptide. This chain is referred as to the latency associated peptide (LAP). UniProtKB:P01137, 30-278, Cys-225, CHEBI:29952.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant R218H, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the latency associated peptide (LAP). UniProtKB:P01137, 279-390, Arg-218, CHEBI:29979.

A TGF-beta 1 sequence variant R218H, signal peptide removed form (human) that has been processed by subsequent removal of the C-terminal mature peptide. This chain is referred as to the latency associated peptide (LAP). This form has decreased affinity for the mature peptide. UniProtKB:P01137, 30-278, Arg-218, CHEBI:29979.
A TGF-beta 2 isoform A that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage and released from the latent complex. This form, cross-linked to an identical chain, is the active mature protein.
A TGF-beta 2 isoform A, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent removal of the C-terminal mature protein. This chain is referred as to the latency associated peptide (LAP).

A TGF-beta 2 isoform A, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent cleavage at the dibasic cleavage site rendering the latency associated peptide (LAP) and the mature protein non-covalently bound.
A TGF-beta 2 isoform B that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage and released from the latent complex. This form is the active mature peptide.

A TGF-beta 2 isoform B, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent cleavage at the dibasic cleavage site rendering the latency associated peptide (LAP) and the mature protein non-covalently bound.
A TGF-beta 3 isoform 1 that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage and released from the latent complex. This form is the active mature peptide.

A TGF-beta 3 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage to remove the C-terminal mature peptide. This chain is referred as to the latency associated peptide (LAP).

A TGF-beta 3 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent cleavage at the dibasic cleavage site rendering the latency associated peptide (LAP) and the mature protein non-covalently bound.

label.value: activin/inhibin beta A chain isoform 1 cleaved 1

value.value: An activin/inhibin beta A chain isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent removal of the propeptide, yielding the mature protein. It is a subunit of inhibin A and activin A complexes. Inhibin A complex is a dimer of INHA and INHBA, whereas activin A complex is a homodimer of INHBA.

label.value: activin/inhibin beta B chain isoform 1 cleaved 1

value.value: An activin/inhibin beta B chain isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent removal of the propeptide, yielding the mature protein. It is a subunit of activin B, inhibin B and activin AB complexes. Activin B is a homodimer of INHBB. Inhibin B is a dimer of INHA and INHBB. Activin AB is a dimer of INHBA and INHBB.

label.value: activin/inhibin beta E chain isoform 1 cleaved 1

value.value: An activin/inhibin beta E chain isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent removal of the propeptide, yielding the mature protein.
A growth/differentiation factor 5 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent removal of the propeptide, yielding the mature protein. The functional unit is a dimer.
A growth/differentiation factor 7 isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent removal of the propeptide, yielding the mature protein.

label.value: inhibin beta C chain isoform 1 cleaved 1

value.value: An inhibin beta C chain isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by subsequent removal of the propeptide, yielding the mature protein. It can form heterodimers with INHBB or INHBA.
A lefty 1 isoform 1 that is the C-terminal part after processing by proteolytic cleavage at the first dibasic RxxR cleavage site within the propeptide region.
